1
00:00:08,291 --> 00:00:10,791
- Lutz: JONAH.
HEY, JONAH!

2
00:00:13,875 --> 00:00:15,833
DAMN, I LOST HIM.

3
00:00:15,916 --> 00:00:17,958
YEAH, OF COURSE I LOST HIM.

4
00:00:18,041 --> 00:00:21,875
THE KID WAS STATIONED WITH
AN ALPINE UNIT. I WAS A COP.

5
00:00:21,958 --> 00:00:24,916
THOUGH I WAS WITH A PRESTIGIOUS
ANTI-TERRORIST TASK FORCE.

6
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:27,958
- Valmet: THIS IS
A HIGH-PRESSURE PAINTBALL GUN.

7
00:00:28,041 --> 00:00:29,625
GETTIN' TAGGED BY ONE HURTS.

8
00:00:29,708 --> 00:00:32,625
- YEAH, I KNOW ALL ABOUT 'EM.

9
00:00:32,708 --> 00:00:35,000
SO, WHAT?  YOU WANT ME
TO TRAIN WITH THAT?

10
00:00:35,083 --> 00:00:37,000
- YOU'RE DAMN STRAIGHT, LUTZ.

11
00:00:37,083 --> 00:00:39,208
PRETTY SURE YOU WERE THE ONLY
ONE TO GET HIT BY ENEMY FIRE--

12
00:00:39,291 --> 00:00:41,125
- ( laughs ) BETTER HIM THAN ME.
- SERIOUSLY.

13
00:00:41,208 --> 00:00:43,541
- TIME FOR A NICE GAME
OF CAPTURE THE FLAG.

14
00:00:43,625 --> 00:00:45,916
YOU AND JONAH--
FIRST TO THE FLAG WINS ALL.

15
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:48,541
- DO I HAVE TO?
I DON'T WANNA SHOOT AT LUTZ.

16
00:00:48,625 --> 00:00:50,375
- ALL RIGHT,
I'LL TELL YOU WHAT.

17
00:00:50,458 --> 00:00:52,750
YOU GET 15 POINTS
FOR EACH SHOT THAT HITS.

18
00:00:52,833 --> 00:00:54,958
AND 30 IF YOU'RE THE FIRST ONE
TO THE FLAG.

19
00:00:55,041 --> 00:00:57,500
AT THE END, I'LL GIVE YOU
A SPECIAL MEAL TICKET

20
00:00:57,583 --> 00:01:00,041
FOR EVERY 50 POINTS YOU SCORE.
NOW, LET'S GO, JONAH.

21
00:01:00,125 --> 00:01:03,458
- Tojo: THAT'S ABOUT
AS EASY AS MATH GETS.

22
00:01:03,541 --> 00:01:06,458
- YOU'RE A GOOD SHOT, LUTZ.
NONE OF US DOUBT THAT.

23
00:01:06,541 --> 00:01:08,625
YOU JUST GOTTA LEARN
MOUNTAIN COMBAT.

24
00:01:08,708 --> 00:01:09,958
COMMENCE OPERATION.

25
00:01:10,041 --> 00:01:11,791
- Lutz:
WHAT WAS I SUPPOSED TO DO,

26
00:01:11,875 --> 00:01:14,125
WITH EVERYBODY GIVING ME
SO MUCH SHIT?

27
00:01:14,208 --> 00:01:16,000
- WIDE OPEN.

28
00:01:16,083 --> 00:01:18,375
- KEEP GETTIN' FLASHES
OF MY SNIPER WORK

29
00:01:18,458 --> 00:01:20,041
SPINNING AROUND MY HEAD.

30
00:01:20,125 --> 00:01:23,000
THE TIMES I TOOK THE SHOT
AND THE TIMES I DIDN'T.

31
00:01:23,083 --> 00:01:25,791
THAT ASSASSIN FROM ORCHESTRA.

32
00:01:25,875 --> 00:01:28,125
AM I A FAILURE 'CAUSE I
COULDN'T SHOOT A LITTLE GIRL?

33
00:01:28,208 --> 00:01:30,208
I WAS TRAINED
FOR SNIPING THUGS

34
00:01:30,291 --> 00:01:32,250
WHO HAVE THEIR GUNS
POINTED AT HOSTAGES,

35
00:01:32,333 --> 00:01:35,041
OR TERRORISTS WHO'VE GOT THEIR
FINGER ON A BOMB SWITCH.

36
00:01:35,125 --> 00:01:37,916
THE SKILLS I LEARNED AS A COP
LET ME BLOW THE BRAINS

37
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:40,875
OUT OF THE WORLD'S SCUM
BEFORE THEY CAN BLINK AN EYE.

38
00:01:40,958 --> 00:01:43,958
NOBODY EVER TRAINED ME
TO SHOOT KIDS.

39
00:01:44,041 --> 00:01:47,416
BUT IF I HAD IT TO DO AGAIN,

40
00:01:47,500 --> 00:01:49,583
IF ANOTHER CHICK LIKE THE ONE
FROM ORCHESTRA SHOWED UP

41
00:01:49,666 --> 00:01:52,333
AND THREATENED
THE BOSS LADY'S LIFE,

42
00:01:52,416 --> 00:01:54,291
COULD I HANDLE THAT?

43
00:01:54,375 --> 00:01:57,083
COULD I MAKE THAT SPLIT-SECOND
DECISION TO SHOOT HER DEAD?

44
00:01:57,166 --> 00:01:58,958
PROBABLY.

45
00:01:59,041 --> 00:02:02,458
I RESPECT KOKO,
AND I WANT TO PROTECT HER.

46
00:02:02,541 --> 00:02:04,500
STILL, WHAT IF THE KID
I HAD TO SHOOT

47
00:02:04,583 --> 00:02:06,083
LOOKED JUST LIKE JONAH?
AHHH!

48
00:02:07,750 --> 00:02:10,958
- ( laughs )
- JONAH!

49
00:02:11,041 --> 00:02:12,750
I'M GONNA KILL YOU!

50
00:02:12,833 --> 00:02:15,125
DAMN IT, GET BACK HERE!

51
00:02:15,208 --> 00:02:18,291
- ( laughs )

52
00:02:18,375 --> 00:02:20,083
- HA HA! CATCHIN' UP!

53
00:02:20,166 --> 00:02:22,458
OW!

54
00:02:22,541 --> 00:02:24,708
THE HELL?
A TRAP?

55
00:02:24,791 --> 00:02:26,750
AHH!

56
00:02:26,833 --> 00:02:28,333
AW, SHIT!

57
00:02:28,416 --> 00:02:29,791
NOOOO!

58
00:02:29,875 --> 00:02:32,000
- Valmet:
TWO, THREE, FOUR...

59
00:02:32,083 --> 00:02:35,125
- THAT'S MY LUTZ.
YOU NEVER LET ME DOWN.

60
00:02:35,208 --> 00:02:37,291
- ...NINE...
- LAUGH IT UP.

61
00:02:37,375 --> 00:02:38,416
IT WAS JUST A GAME.

62
00:02:38,500 --> 00:02:40,833
IT'S NOT LIKE
I WAS REALLY TRYING.

63
00:02:40,916 --> 00:02:42,416
- News anchor:
TERRITORY DISPUTES STILL HAVE

64
00:02:42,500 --> 00:02:45,125
TENSIONS RUNNING HIGH BETWEEN
MIDDLE EASTERN COUNTRY A

65
00:02:45,208 --> 00:02:46,666
AND EUROPEAN COUNTRY B.

66
00:02:46,750 --> 00:02:49,000
AN INTERNATIONAL COMMUNICATIONS
COMPANY REPORTS

67
00:02:49,083 --> 00:02:50,958
THAT COUNTRY A'S
MILITARY HAS GATHERED

68
00:02:51,041 --> 00:02:52,250
AT THE LINE OF CONFLICT--
- VALMET, COME ON.

69
00:02:52,333 --> 00:02:53,583
IT'S TIME TO GET UP.

70
00:02:53,666 --> 00:02:55,291
- OH, GOOD MORNING.

71
00:02:55,375 --> 00:02:57,625
DON'T WE HAVE A MEETING
ON THE AGENDA TODAY?

72
00:02:57,708 --> 00:02:59,041
- YES.

73
00:02:59,125 --> 00:03:01,250
THE UNMANNED AERIAL VEHICLE
SUPPLY COMMITTEE

74
00:03:01,333 --> 00:03:03,583
IS MEETING AT
COUNTRY B'S EMBASSY IN LONDON.

75
00:03:03,666 --> 00:03:06,833
- THIS COMMITTEE IS DEDICATED
TO INTRODUCING

76
00:03:06,916 --> 00:03:10,416
UNMANNED AERIAL VEHICLES AT
LAST TO COUNTRY B'S AIR FORCE.

77
00:03:10,500 --> 00:03:13,583
WE WILL BE LOOKING AT H.C.L.I.'S
AMERICAN-MADE PREDATOR

78
00:03:13,666 --> 00:03:16,458
AND THE EURO GROUP'S
NEURON PROJECT--

79
00:03:16,541 --> 00:03:18,666
- DID YOU CHECK OUT
WHO THE COMPETITION'S

80
00:03:18,750 --> 00:03:19,750
THROWING AT US TODAY?

81
00:03:19,833 --> 00:03:22,666
- Koko: WOW.
- AMALIA TOROHOVSKY--

82
00:03:22,750 --> 00:03:24,708
ACTRESS TURNED ARMS DEALER.

83
00:03:24,791 --> 00:03:26,708
- SHE'S BEAUTIFUL, HUH?

84
00:03:26,791 --> 00:03:29,333
- ( Russian accent )
KOKO HEKMATYAR!

85
00:03:29,416 --> 00:03:31,875
MY GOODNESS, WHAT A PLEASURE.

86
00:03:31,958 --> 00:03:33,000
I HEARD THERE WAS
GOING TO BE

87
00:03:33,083 --> 00:03:34,666
A SWEET, FRESH-FACED
DEALER HERE TODAY

88
00:03:34,750 --> 00:03:36,958
AND I SIMPLY
HAD TO SEE FOR MYSELF.

89
00:03:37,041 --> 00:03:39,708
SO THE RUMORS ARE TRUE.
DO GO EASY ON ME.

90
00:03:39,791 --> 00:03:41,875
- OH, SURE.

91
00:03:41,958 --> 00:03:45,833
- ( theme music playing )

92
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:16,375
- ( singing in Japanese )

93
00:05:11,958 --> 00:05:14,791
- Koko: THIS SUCKS.
A LOT.

94
00:05:14,875 --> 00:05:16,541
LISTEN TO THIS, JONAH.

95
00:05:16,625 --> 00:05:18,791
- I DON'T THINK TELLING ME
WILL MAKE IT ANY BETTER.

96
00:05:18,875 --> 00:05:21,291
- I'M GOING TO ANYWAY.
( laughs )

97
00:05:22,916 --> 00:05:25,000
THE COMPETITION IS FORMIDABLE
ON THIS TRIP.

98
00:05:25,083 --> 00:05:28,791
IT'S LIKE THE DEAL HAD ALREADY
BEEN MADE BY THE TIME I ARRIVED,

99
00:05:28,875 --> 00:05:30,250
LIKE I'D BEEN
TAKEN OUT OF THE GAME

100
00:05:30,333 --> 00:05:32,333
BEFORE I EVEN STARTED TO PLAY.

101
00:05:32,416 --> 00:05:34,583
THE RUMORS WERE RIGHT
ABOUT THAT WOMAN.

102
00:05:34,666 --> 00:05:36,708
SHE MOVES FAST.
- WHAT WOMAN?

103
00:05:36,791 --> 00:05:40,125
- OH, THIS MEGA-HOT ACTRESS
TURNED ARMS DEALER.

104
00:05:40,208 --> 00:05:41,833
ALL SHE HAS TO DO
IS CROOK HER FINGER

105
00:05:41,916 --> 00:05:42,875
AND THOSE
OLD MILITARY BOYS

106
00:05:42,958 --> 00:05:45,125
COME RUNNING
TO BUY HER MERCHANDISE.

107
00:05:45,208 --> 00:05:47,375
HER FAME LANDED HER
A WEALTHY HUSBAND,

108
00:05:47,458 --> 00:05:49,458
BUT HER STAR FADED,
HE PASSED AWAY,

109
00:05:49,541 --> 00:05:52,333
AND HIS ENTIRE FORTUNE
WENT TO HER.

110
00:05:52,416 --> 00:05:54,916
SO NOW SHE'S USING
HER CONSIDERABLE CHARM

111
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:57,333
TO WORK HER WAY UP
IN THE WEAPONS TRADE.

112
00:05:57,416 --> 00:05:59,583
SHE DOES SEEM LIKE A WEIRD ONE,
THOUGH.

113
00:05:59,666 --> 00:06:01,625
FEW ROUNDS SHORT
OF A FULL CLIP.

114
00:06:01,708 --> 00:06:03,708
- WHAT PRODUCT DO YOU HAVE
ON THE TABLE NOW?

115
00:06:03,791 --> 00:06:06,208
- BRAND NEW U.A.V.s--
RADIO-CONTROLLED PLANES

116
00:06:06,291 --> 00:06:08,583
USED FOR SCOUTING
AND RECONNAISSANCE.

117
00:06:08,666 --> 00:06:10,916
THESE BABIES NEVER GET TIRED
OR CARELESS.

118
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:13,250
AND NOBODY DIES
IF ONE GETS SHOT DOWN.

119
00:06:13,333 --> 00:06:15,916
WHEN EQUIPPED WITH WEAPONS,
IT CAN EVEN BE USED IN COMBAT.

120
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:17,375
JUST RECENTLY,
IN FACT, ONE WAS USED

121
00:06:17,458 --> 00:06:19,583
TO BOMB A CERTAIN ORGANIZATION.

122
00:06:19,666 --> 00:06:21,208
WE ARE LIVING IN
AN AGE WHERE ROBOTS

123
00:06:21,291 --> 00:06:22,541
ARE USED TO KILL HUMANS.

124
00:06:22,625 --> 00:06:25,083
I'M SURE ISAAC ASIMOV
IS ROLLING IN HIS GRAVE.

125
00:06:25,166 --> 00:06:27,916
- I'M NOT SURE I LIKE THE SOUND
OF THOSE THINGS.

126
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:29,875
- HEY, I'M WITH YOU
ON THAT PART.

127
00:06:29,958 --> 00:06:31,375
THEY CREEP ME OUT TOO.

128
00:06:31,458 --> 00:06:33,166
BUT MY JOB
IS TO SELL THE SUCKERS,

129
00:06:33,250 --> 00:06:34,750
REGARDLESS OF
MY PERSONAL FEELINGS.

130
00:06:34,833 --> 00:06:37,166
- HEY, KOKO!

131
00:06:37,250 --> 00:06:39,375
UGH, THIS PLACE.
IT'S FREAKIN' HUMID

132
00:06:39,458 --> 00:06:42,000
AND THE SKY'S ALWAYS CLOUDY
AND THE FOOD IS DISGUSTING.

133
00:06:42,083 --> 00:06:44,166
- Koko: BE NICE.
- YEAH SO,

134
00:06:44,250 --> 00:06:46,708
ABOUT THIS WHOLE
PREDATOR SITUATION,

135
00:06:46,791 --> 00:06:49,416
THE AMERICANS
ARE NOT INTERESTED.

136
00:06:49,500 --> 00:06:51,916
LET ME SEE
IF I'VE GOT YOUR BASIC IDEA.

137
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:54,500
THE U.S. SELLS U.A.V.s
TO COUNTRY A

138
00:06:54,583 --> 00:06:56,000
WITH THE UNDERSTANDING
THAT THEY'LL BE USED

139
00:06:56,083 --> 00:06:57,541
TO SETTLE CIVIL UNREST.

140
00:06:57,625 --> 00:07:00,291
THIS, IN TURN, WILL PISS OFF
NEIGHBORING COUNTRY B,

141
00:07:00,375 --> 00:07:03,333
AT WHICH POINT THE U.S. WILL
OFFER TO SELL TO THEM AS WELL.

142
00:07:03,416 --> 00:07:05,375
TO MAINTAIN THE BALANCE
OF POWER, RIGHT?

143
00:07:05,458 --> 00:07:07,375
YOUR PLAN
HAS ONE MINOR FLAW, THOUGH.

144
00:07:07,458 --> 00:07:09,291
COUNTRY B
IS ALREADY IN THE PROCESS

145
00:07:09,375 --> 00:07:12,375
OF DEVELOPING THEIR OWN U.A.V.s
WITH THE NEURON PROJECT.

146
00:07:12,458 --> 00:07:14,541
THE AMERICANS FIGURE
THIS WILL RESOLVE ITSELF

147
00:07:14,625 --> 00:07:16,375
ON ITS OWN WITHOUT THEIR HELP.

148
00:07:16,458 --> 00:07:17,875
- THE U.A.V. MARKET

149
00:07:17,958 --> 00:07:19,958
IS JUST GONNA KEEP
GETTING HOTTER AND HOTTER.

150
00:07:20,041 --> 00:07:22,333
IT'S ALWAYS BETTER TO BE
THE ONE FEEDING THE FIRE

151
00:07:22,416 --> 00:07:24,625
THAN GETTING BURNED BY IT,
WOULDN'T YOU AGREE?

152
00:07:24,708 --> 00:07:27,333
- I GOTTA GET GOING.
YOU KNOW SCARECROW.

153
00:07:27,416 --> 00:07:30,000
HE'LL PISS HIMSELF IF I SPEND
TOO MUCH TIME WITH YOU.

154
00:07:30,083 --> 00:07:32,833
- HMM.
- WHA-- WHAT'S WRONG?

155
00:07:32,916 --> 00:07:35,416
- I FIND IT INTERESTING
THAT A C.I.A. TECHIE

156
00:07:35,500 --> 00:07:37,458
WOULD JOIN UP WITH SCARECROW.

157
00:07:37,541 --> 00:07:39,625
HIS CRUSADE AGAINST ME
IS PATHETIC.

158
00:07:39,708 --> 00:07:42,041
BUT THAT'S OKAY,
I WON'T STOP YOU.

159
00:07:42,125 --> 00:07:45,166
IN FACT, I THINK YOU AND I ARE
GOING TO GET ALONG QUITE WELL.

160
00:07:45,250 --> 00:07:48,083
- UM, THIS--
THIS CAN'T BE A--

161
00:07:48,166 --> 00:07:51,375
OH, HOLY CRAP, IT IS.

162
00:07:51,458 --> 00:07:53,375
AWESOME!
IS IT FOR ME?

163
00:07:53,458 --> 00:07:55,791
- I DON'T WANT THE AMERICANS
PULLING OUT OF THIS DEAL,

164
00:07:55,875 --> 00:07:58,208
SO YOU'LL KEEP AN EYE ON THEM
FOR ME, RIGHT?

165
00:07:58,291 --> 00:08:01,416
- SHE'S TOTALLY USING ME.

166
00:08:01,500 --> 00:08:04,291
I'M PROBABLY GETTING MYSELF
INTO AN UGLY SITUATION.

167
00:08:04,375 --> 00:08:07,000
OH, WELL, WHATEV.
SURE.

168
00:08:07,083 --> 00:08:08,625
- Koko:
UGO, LET'S SWING BY THE HOTELS

169
00:08:08,708 --> 00:08:10,708
THAT ARE ACCOMMODATING
COUNTRY B'S PEOPLE.

170
00:08:10,791 --> 00:08:12,041
- YOU GOT IT.

171
00:08:12,125 --> 00:08:14,416
- GET READY TO ROCK, BOYS!
WE'VE GOT STUFF TO SELL.

172
00:08:14,500 --> 00:08:16,416
- DAMN.
LITTLE LADY'S ON FIRE TODAY.

173
00:08:16,500 --> 00:08:19,125
- MS. KOKO HEKMATYAR
OF H.C.L.I.?

174
00:08:19,208 --> 00:08:21,166
IF YOU'LL WAIT IN THE LOBBY,
PLEASE.

175
00:08:21,250 --> 00:08:22,666
- ( door dings )

176
00:08:24,500 --> 00:08:27,875
- GENERA-- OH!
- MS. HEKMATYAR.

177
00:08:27,958 --> 00:08:31,208
WELL, I'M SURE YOU CAN SEE
HOW THINGS STAND.

178
00:08:31,291 --> 00:08:35,958
SORRY.
- ( chuckles )

179
00:08:36,041 --> 00:08:38,583
- Man: MY APOLOGIES,
MS. HEKMATYAR.

180
00:08:38,666 --> 00:08:40,041
I KNOW YOU WERE
SCHEDULED TO MEET WITH

181
00:08:40,125 --> 00:08:41,750
THE COLONEL THIS AFTERNOON,
BUT I'M AFRAID

182
00:08:41,833 --> 00:08:43,583
HE HAS BEEN
UNAVOIDABLY DETAINED.

183
00:08:43,666 --> 00:08:46,750
- RIGHT.
- Man #2: I AM VERY SORRY.

184
00:08:46,833 --> 00:08:48,875
THE LIEUTENANT GENERAL
HAS ALREADY LEFT.

185
00:08:48,958 --> 00:08:50,375
HE'LL BE GONE FOR THE DAY.
- LOVELY.

186
00:08:50,458 --> 00:08:52,708
- Man #3: INITIALLY,
I WAS ONE OF THE ONES

187
00:08:52,791 --> 00:08:54,458
PUSHING FOR THE PREDATORS.
IN THE END,

188
00:08:54,541 --> 00:08:56,000
THE EURO GROUP
WON ME OVER, THOUGH.

189
00:08:56,083 --> 00:08:58,458
WE NEED TO STICK
WITH EUROPEAN TECHNOLOGY.

190
00:08:58,541 --> 00:09:00,208
- OF COURSE.

191
00:09:00,291 --> 00:09:02,875
( grunting )

192
00:09:02,958 --> 00:09:05,916
THAT BITCH
IS EVERYWHERE!

193
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:08,541
- SEEN HER GET HER PANTIES
IN A TWIST, BUT HER WHOLE BODY?

194
00:09:08,625 --> 00:09:10,333
- REMINDS ME
OF RODIN'S THE THINKER.

195
00:09:10,416 --> 00:09:12,541
- ONE PLACE LEFT.
LET'S ROLL.

196
00:09:12,625 --> 00:09:14,875
- Ugo: WHO IS IT?
- LIEUTENANT COLONEL MARQUIS

197
00:09:14,958 --> 00:09:16,333
FROM COUNTRY B'S ARMY.

198
00:09:16,416 --> 00:09:17,875
HE'S BEEN A SUPPORTER
OF THE PREDATORS.

199
00:09:17,958 --> 00:09:20,083
AND HE'S WORKED WITH US BEFORE.

200
00:09:20,166 --> 00:09:23,083
- MS. TOROHOVSKY PAID ME A VISIT
EARLIER AS WELL,

201
00:09:23,166 --> 00:09:25,541
BUT I HAVE WITHHELD
MAKING A DECISION.

202
00:09:25,625 --> 00:09:27,125
- I APPRECIATE THAT.

203
00:09:27,208 --> 00:09:29,416
- YOU COULD TAKE IT
AS A COMPLIMENT.

204
00:09:29,500 --> 00:09:31,291
MAYBE SHE'S MOVING QUICKLY
BECAUSE SHE KNOWS

205
00:09:31,375 --> 00:09:32,875
YOU'RE A WORTHY OPPONENT.

206
00:09:32,958 --> 00:09:36,041
I IMAGINE H.C.L.I. HEADQUARTERS
HAS ALREADY INFORMED YOU,

207
00:09:36,125 --> 00:09:38,250
BUT AN ITALIAN NEWSPAPER
WROTE AN EXPOSE

208
00:09:38,333 --> 00:09:40,000
ON YOUR IMPORTATION PLAN.

209
00:09:40,083 --> 00:09:44,500
- THE NEWSPAPER IS REALLY
NOTHING BETTER THAN A TABLOID.

210
00:09:44,583 --> 00:09:46,666
- IF THIS DOESN'T WORK,
WE'LL LEAK THE INFO

211
00:09:46,750 --> 00:09:48,500
TO A LEGITIMATE PAPER
AND FINISH HER OFF.

212
00:09:48,583 --> 00:09:50,666
- Amalia: KOKO WAS SMART.

213
00:09:50,750 --> 00:09:53,416
SAYING THE PREDATORS
ACQUIRED HAD BEEN DISPOSED OF

214
00:09:53,500 --> 00:09:55,875
BY THE ITALIAN AIR FORCE
AND INSISTING THAT THE U.S.

215
00:09:55,958 --> 00:09:58,333
WAS NOT DIRECTLY
PROVIDING THE AIRCRAFTS.

216
00:09:58,416 --> 00:10:00,041
SHE HELPS COUNTRY A SAVE FACE

217
00:10:00,125 --> 00:10:02,500
BY MAKING IT LOOK
LIKE CIVILIANS MADE THE DEAL.

218
