OF THE E.A.E.

426
00:18:41,125 --> 00:18:43,000
RUN BACK TO HIS HOME COUNTRY.

427
00:18:43,083 --> 00:18:45,083
HE WAS SO ANGRY,
I WAS CONVINCED

428
00:18:45,166 --> 00:18:47,666
HE WAS GOING TO HAVE A STROKE
RIGHT IN FRONT OF ME.

429
00:18:47,750 --> 00:18:50,875
I DON'T DO WHAT I DO BECAUSE
I'M FIGHTING FOR SOME CAUSE

430
00:18:50,958 --> 00:18:53,291
OR BECAUSE I HAVE
A FAMILY TO SUPPORT.

431
00:18:53,375 --> 00:18:55,791
NO, I DO IT
BECAUSE I LIKE THE RUSH.

432
00:18:55,875 --> 00:18:57,916
IT'S LESS AND LESS
OFTEN THESE DAYS

433
00:18:58,000 --> 00:18:59,208
THAT YOU COME ACROSS
SOMEONE WHO CAN THROW

434
00:18:59,291 --> 00:19:02,833
A REALLY STRONG PUNCH,
LET ALONE ANOTHER WOMAN.

435
00:19:02,916 --> 00:19:05,375
I'M HAVING A GREAT TIME,
HONESTLY.

436
00:19:05,458 --> 00:19:07,875
THIS IS THE KIND OF THING
I LIVE FOR--

437
00:19:07,958 --> 00:19:10,041
FUN CHATS LIKE THIS.

438
00:19:10,125 --> 00:19:12,583
ALL YOUR WORK HAS PAID OFF,
KOKO.

439
00:19:12,666 --> 00:19:15,125
WE ARE PULLING OUT
OF THE U.A.V. SALES CAMPAIGN.

440
00:19:15,208 --> 00:19:18,041
THE EURO GROUP CONCEDES DEFEAT
TO YOU THIS TIME AROUND.

441
00:19:18,125 --> 00:19:21,208
- ( laughs )
IT WAS A TOUGH BATTLE.

442
00:19:21,291 --> 00:19:23,916
- "YESTERDAY'S ENEMY,
TOMORROW'S FRIEND."

443
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:26,000
THAT IS THE EUROPEAN WAY
OF THINKING.

444
00:19:26,083 --> 00:19:29,791
- ( thinking ) OH JEEZ.
- YOU AGREE WITH ME, DON'T YOU?

445
00:19:29,875 --> 00:19:32,500
ENEMIES TODAY
CAN BECOME FRIENDS TOMORROW.

446
00:19:32,583 --> 00:19:34,583
- NO NEED TO REPEAT IT.
I HEARD YOU THE FIRST TIME.

447
00:19:34,666 --> 00:19:36,375
NOW, WHY DID YOU
WANT TO MEET ME?

448
00:19:36,458 --> 00:19:38,791
- ABOUT E.A.E.'S STOCK.

449
00:19:38,875 --> 00:19:41,333
CAN YOU PLEASE DO SOMETHING?
AS A FRIEND?

450
00:19:41,416 --> 00:19:42,833
- WHAT A SURPRISE.

451
00:19:42,916 --> 00:19:45,125
COME NOW, SURELY YOU KNOW
THAT'S NOT THE WAY THIS WORKS.

452
00:19:45,208 --> 00:19:47,708
LET'S REFER BACK TO THAT
DISCUSSION WE HAD A MINUTE AGO.

453
00:19:47,791 --> 00:19:51,250
I AM WELL AWARE
OF HOW EUROPEANS DO THINGS.

454
00:19:51,333 --> 00:19:52,666
BUT I THINK IT
MAY BE TIME FOR YOU

455
00:19:52,750 --> 00:19:54,625
TO RECONSIDER YOUR METHODS.

456
00:19:54,708 --> 00:19:56,500
WE NEED TO DON OUR MASKS

457
00:19:56,583 --> 00:19:59,416
AND STRIKE OUT AT OUR
MUTUAL ENEMIES. THAT'S RIGHT.

458
00:19:59,500 --> 00:20:03,166
THE RECENTLY PRIVATIZED
NATIONAL DEFENSE COMPANIES.

459
00:20:03,250 --> 00:20:06,625
AS WE CAN SEE FROM THE SITUATION
WE JUST FOUND OURSELVES IN,

460
00:20:06,708 --> 00:20:09,875
THEY WILL ONLY SERVE
TO HOLD THE WHOLE GROUP BACK.

461
00:20:09,958 --> 00:20:12,833
THEY THINK OF THEMSELVES
AS UNSINKABLE WARSHIPS,

462
00:20:12,916 --> 00:20:15,791
AND THAT KIND OF CONFIDENCE
DOESN'T VANISH OVERNIGHT.

463
00:20:15,875 --> 00:20:18,208
INVERSELY, THAT WILL--
- Amalia: WOULD YOU CONSIDER

464
00:20:18,291 --> 00:20:22,291
SELLING IT BACK AT 2.5%
OF YOUR T.O.B. PURCHASE PRICE?

465
00:20:22,375 --> 00:20:24,208
- WERE YOU EVEN LISTENING TO ME?

466
00:20:24,291 --> 00:20:26,833
THE BEST I CAN OFFER IS 10%.
- 5%.

467
00:20:26,916 --> 00:20:30,166
- ( thinking ) THIS IS INSANE.
I CAN'T BELIEVE THESE WOMEN.

468
00:20:30,250 --> 00:20:32,541
THEY'RE CASUALLY DECIDING
THE FATE OF THE ENTIRE E.A.E.

469
00:20:32,625 --> 00:20:34,750
IN SOME FILTHY BACK ALLEY.

470
00:20:34,833 --> 00:20:36,625
( aloud )
SNIPER ONE, SNIPER TWO,

471
00:20:36,708 --> 00:20:38,958
TAKE POSITION AND PREPARE
TO FIRE. DO YOU COPY?

472
00:20:39,041 --> 00:20:39,958
- ROGER.
- ROGER.

473
00:20:42,666 --> 00:20:44,708
- KOKO.
- YOU ARE CLEAR TO FIRE.

474
00:20:54,833 --> 00:20:57,500
EXCELLENT SHOOTING, LUTZ.

475
00:20:57,583 --> 00:21:00,791
- ( Wilee laughs ) THEY DON'T
EVEN KNOW WHAT HIT 'EM.

476
00:21:00,875 --> 00:21:03,583
BADASS.
YOU REALLY ARE GOOD, LUTZ.

477
00:21:03,666 --> 00:21:07,333
- THE 270 METERS
ACROSS THE RIVER ISN'T THAT FAR.

478
00:21:07,416 --> 00:21:10,958
EVEN LEHM
COULD HAVE GOTTEN IT DONE.

479
00:21:11,041 --> 00:21:12,458
- SORRY TO STARTLE YOU.

480
00:21:12,541 --> 00:21:14,500
WE HAD SOME TROUBLEMAKERS
TO DEAL WITH.

481
00:21:14,583 --> 00:21:15,791
BUT WE DIDN'T KILL THEM.

482
00:21:19,500 --> 00:21:23,375
I AM WILLING TO SELL, BUT ONLY
IF IT'S DIRECTLY TO YOU.

483
00:21:23,458 --> 00:21:26,000
WHAT DO YOU SAY?
HOW DOES 5% SOUND?

484
00:21:26,083 --> 00:21:29,500
- THAT SOUNDS MORE THAN FAIR,
KOKO.

485
00:21:29,583 --> 00:21:32,458
- I THOUGHT IT MIGHT.
SEE YOU AT THE EMBASSY TOMORROW.

486
00:21:35,875 --> 00:21:37,583
- Valmet: I DON'T GET IT.

487
00:21:37,666 --> 00:21:40,000
WHY WERE YOU SO SOFT
ON THAT WOMAN?  UGH!

488
00:21:40,083 --> 00:21:42,000
- YEAH.
I DON'T KNOW.

489
00:21:42,083 --> 00:21:44,458
MAYBE IT'S BECAUSE SHE SAID
IT WAS FUN TALKING TO ME.

490
00:21:44,541 --> 00:21:46,208
- THEN I MUST BE HAVING
A MILLION TIMES MORE FUN

491
00:21:46,291 --> 00:21:47,833
THAN SHE EVER WILL!

492
00:21:47,916 --> 00:21:50,291
- VALMET, I THINK IT'S SAFER
IF YOU WATCH THE ROAD.

493
00:21:50,375 --> 00:21:54,041
MAN,
TOROHOVSKY WAS A REAL HANDFUL.

494
00:21:54,125 --> 00:21:57,125
RATHER NOT BUTT HEADS
WITH HER AGAIN IF I CAN HELP IT.

495
00:21:57,208 --> 00:22:00,791
BUT PEOPLE LIKE THAT ALWAYS SEEM
TO REAPPEAR SOMEHOW.

496
00:22:00,875 --> 00:22:03,458
THEY COME OUT OF THE WOODWORK
WHEN YOU LEAST EXPECT IT.

497
00:22:03,541 --> 00:22:04,916
CONSIDERING HOW BIG
THIS PLANET IS,

498
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:07,291
IT'S A SMALL FREAKIN' WORLD.

